<item>
            <title>[FLINK-24353] Bash scripts do not respect dynamic configurations when calculating memory sizes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-24353</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Dynamic configurations (the &apos;-D&apos; arguments) are lost due to changes in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-21128&quot; title=&quot;Rethink how Kubernetes interfaces with our docker image&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-21128&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-21128&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Consequently, dynamic configurations like the following commands will not take effect.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
./bin/taskmanager.sh start -D taskmanager.memory.task.off-heap.size=128m
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
