                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17418462" author="zentol" created="Wed, 22 Sep 2021 07:36:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Shouldn&apos;t it be &lt;tt&gt;./bin/taskmanager.sh start -Dtaskmanager.memory.task.off-heap.size=128m&lt;/tt&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17418471" author="xintongsong" created="Wed, 22 Sep 2021 08:19:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think both `&lt;tt&gt;-Dkey=value&lt;/tt&gt;` and `&lt;tt&gt;-D key=value&lt;/tt&gt;` are expected to work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I tried this on &lt;tt&gt;taskmanager.numberOfTaskSlots&lt;/tt&gt; and both ways work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, for memory options, &lt;del&gt;only `&lt;tt&gt;-Dkey=value&lt;/tt&gt;` works but not `&lt;tt&gt;-D key=value&lt;/tt&gt;`&lt;/del&gt;&#160;neither way works.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
